name: The Neon Arts Of Yowatashi Boshi

metadata.name: Neon Shinto of Mars 火星
metadata.description:
Do you know the Japanese symbols for these two Kanji ("火" and "星") stand for fire and celestial object, but together 火星 is called Mars? So another fantastic way to say the meaning of Mars in Japanese can be called "Planet of Fire".
